Cold War Begins
NATO, Warsaw Pact, Berlin: Airlift and Wall
NATO: North Atlantic Treaty Organization
- West European countries
- Protection against Germany, USSR/Soviet Union, communism
- April 4, 1949: 12 members
- Article 5: An attack against one member nation is against us all
- 1955: Western Germany
Warsaw Pact
- 7 countries signed with Soviet Union/USSR
- Counterbalanced NATO
- Proxy Wars - no direct fights, spreading Ideas
Berlin Airlift
- In Soviet Berlin
- USSR closed roads, rails, and canals from the West
- Allies airlifted more than 2.3 million tons of cargo
Berlin Wall
- August 1961, East Side built a Wall dividing Berlin
- 12 foot tall
- 4 foot thick
- Stopped travel bet
